"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5469492-2024-05-08-chinese-doping-scandal-olympic-swimming\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympics The controversy following a report last month that revealed positive drug tests in Chinese swimmers in the lead-up to the Tokyo Olympics continued to escalate in the past week, with the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) standing by its handling of the situation amid growing criticism from the United States Anti-Doping Agency (USADA) and elsewhere.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"The controversy\", \"from\": 9, \"to\": 24}, {\"ngram\": \"a report\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 43}, {\"ngram\": \"positive drug tests\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 88}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead-up\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 123}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"the past week\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"its handling\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"growing criticism\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement With less than 12 weeks until theswimmingcompetition begins at the 2024Olympicsin Paris, the issue has renewed questions of transparency in policing doping and sparked a war of words between major governing agencies, all at a high-profile time.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 458, \"end\": 463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 3.0581713760325735e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"less than 12 weeks\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"theswimmingcompetition\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 427}, {\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"a war\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"words\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"major governing agencies\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"a high-profile time\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On April 20,reporting from The New York Timesand German broadcaster ARD revealed that 23 Chinese swimmers tested positive for a banned substance seven months before the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 - and were never punished.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999999141437, \"rank\": 8.582823926253005e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9774378907015988, \"rank\": 0.02029606428663748, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6555874361801795e-14, \"text\": \"ARD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Das_Erste\"}, {\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned substance\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The banned substance was trimetazidine (TMZ), a prescription heart drug that can enhance performance by increasing blood flow to the heart.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The banned substance\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"a prescription heart drug\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"blood flow\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the athletes who tested positive went on to medal in Tokyo, performances that included three gold medals.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999986718649, \"rank\": 1.3281328090800516e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"medal\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1039}, {\"ngram\": \"performances\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold medals\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The swimmers were allowed to compete in theOlympicsafter WADA accepted China's findings that suggested the Chinese swimmers unwittingly ingested the substance from food they ate at a hotel in Shijiazhuang, in the country's Hebei Province.\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999924851245366, \"rank\": 7.51475080168256e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1484756123324373e-26, \"text\": \"Shijiazhuang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hebei Province\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hebei\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The swimmers\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympicsafter WADA\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"a hotel\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinese investigators did not say how the banned substance got into the hotel's kitchen.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the banned substance\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel's kitchen\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two months after the swimmers tested positive, investigators reported finding trace amounts of the substance in spice containers, sink drains and extractor vents in the hotel's kitchen, an explanation that many anti-doping experts question.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"investigators\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"trace amounts\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"spice containers\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"sink drains\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"extractor vents\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel's kitchen\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"an explanation\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"many anti-doping experts\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a 61-page report compiled by those investigators and reviewed by The New York Times, 60 tests were conducted on 39 swimmers, whose urine samples produced 28 positives involving 23 swimmers.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.280274371634239e-27, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 61-page report\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"those investigators\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"60 tests\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"39 swimmers\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"whose urine samples\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"28 positives\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"23 swimmers\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the samples tested positive for the same drug - TMZ.\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the samples\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1888}, {\"ngram\": \"the same drug\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"- TMZ\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Questions remain regarding how Chinese authorities handled the samples, which were supposed to be immediately sent to an accredited laboratory that would analyze findings and report them to WADA and World Aquatics, the sport's international governing body.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Questions\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"the samples\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2001}, {\"ngram\": \"an accredited laboratory\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"findings\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's international governing body\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The results were not reported to the tracking site until two months after the samples were taken.\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The results\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"the tracking site\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"the samples\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Even trace amounts of this banned substance are supposed to register as a failed drug test and prompt punishment.\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"amounts\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2319}, {\"ngram\": \"this banned substance\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"a failed drug test\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The chain of events that followed the testing differed significantly from what happened a year later when Russian figure skater Kamila Valieva tested positive for TMZ (and also blamed contaminated food).\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.998497950027081, \"rank\": 0.0014878015638136353, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2579, \"end\": 2582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.820405184735813e-32, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The chain\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"the testing\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"contaminated food\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In that circumstance, WADA immediately challenged the Russian anti-doping agency's decision to clear her, and she was ultimatelygiven a four-year ban.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2674, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian anti-doping agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that circumstance\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2646}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-year ban\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in the lead-up to Tokyo, there were no suspensions and no public disclosures.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2794, \"end\": 2799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999986718649, \"rank\": 1.3281328090800516e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the lead-up\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"no suspensions\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2826}, {\"ngram\": \"no public disclosures\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA did not stop any of the swimmers who tested positive from competing in an Olympic qualifying event and ultimately the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2858}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic qualifying event\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 2957}, {\"ngram\": \"ultimately the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The day of the Times' report, WADA releaseda lengthy statementdefending its decision to accept the conclusions made by the China Anti-Doping Agency (CHINADA) - that the swimmers had tested positive in early 2021 for TMZ after inadvertently being exposed to the substance through contamination.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999924851245366, \"rank\": 7.51475080168256e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The day\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"the Times' report\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3021}, {\"ngram\": \"its decision\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"the conclusions\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3103}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3149}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3212}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3263}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement emphasized their review process and said that an on-the-ground inquiry was not possible due to COVID-19 restrictions.\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The statement\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3300}, {\"ngram\": \"their review process\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3332}, {\"ngram\": \"the-ground\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"COVID-19 restrictions\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA ultimately concluded that it was not in a position to disprove the possibility that contamination was the source of TMZ and it was compatible with the analytical data in the file,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3626, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3425}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3504}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3523}, {\"ngram\": \"the source\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3538}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 3542, \"to\": 3545}, {\"ngram\": \"the analytical data\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3592}, {\"ngram\": \"the file\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"the statement\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA also concluded that, given the specific circumstances of the asserted contamination, the athletes would be held to have no fault or negligence.\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3632}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific circumstances\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3686}, {\"ngram\": \"the asserted contamination\", \"from\": 3690, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3730}, {\"ngram\": \"no fault\", \"from\": 3753, \"to\": 3761}, {\"ngram\": \"negligence\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3775}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, and based on the advice of external counsel, WADA considered that an appeal was not warranted.\\\"\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the advice\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3809}, {\"ngram\": \"external counsel\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3829}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3835}, {\"ngram\": \"an appeal\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA also said it was asked in 2022 by the International Testing Agency to review its sample collection and reporting process, and that an independent review \\\"concluded that proper procedures had been followed and that there was no evidence of wrongdoing.\\\"\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 4139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3926, \"end\": 3954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Testing Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3887}, {\"ngram\": \"its sample collection and reporting process\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 4008}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent review\", \"from\": 4019, \"to\": 4040}, {\"ngram\": \"proper procedures\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4074}, {\"ngram\": \"no evidence\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4123}, {\"ngram\": \"wrongdoing\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement WADA also threatened to take legal action against those publishing \\\"misleading and potentially defamatory\\\" coverage of the events.\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisement WADA\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4159}, {\"ngram\": \"legal action\", \"from\": 4184, \"to\": 4196}, {\"ngram\": \"those publishing\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4221}, {\"ngram\": \"misleading and potentially defamatory\\\" coverage\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4270}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 4274, \"to\": 4284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same day, Travis Tygart, the CEO of the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency, went scorched earth.\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4302, \"end\": 4315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the CEO\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4324}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"scorched earth\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is disappointing to see WADA stoop to threats and scare tactics when confronted with a blatant violation of the rules governing anti-doping,\\\" Tygartsaid in a statement.\", \"from\": 4379, \"to\": 4551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA stoop\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4417}, {\"ngram\": \"threats\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4428}, {\"ngram\": \"scare tactics\", \"from\": 4433, \"to\": 4446}, {\"ngram\": \"a blatant violation\", \"from\": 4468, \"to\": 4487}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4500}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you blow away their rhetoric, the facts remain as have been reported: WADA failed to provisionally suspend the athletes, disqualify results, and publicly disclose the positives.\", \"from\": 4552, \"to\": 4735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their rhetoric\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4586}, {\"ngram\": \"the facts\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4597}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 4628, \"to\": 4632}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4697}, {\"ngram\": \"the positives\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 4734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are egregious failures, even if you buy their story that this was contamination and a potent drug 'magically appeared' in a kitchen and led to 23 positive tests of elite Chinese swimmers.\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4912, \"end\": 4919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999895567343244, \"rank\": 1.0422876702503528e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"egregious failures\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4764}, {\"ngram\": \"their story\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4793}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4821}, {\"ngram\": \"a potent drug\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4839}, {\"ngram\": \"a kitchen\", \"from\": 4864, \"to\": 4873}, {\"ngram\": \"23 positive tests\", \"from\": 4885, \"to\": 4902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 \\\"Transparency is the key to shining the light in the darkness, and here, by not following the rules, WADA and CHINADA have left clean athletes in the dark.\\\"\", \"from\": 4930, \"to\": 5089, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transparency\", \"from\": 4933, \"to\": 4945}, {\"ngram\": \"the key\", \"from\": 4949, \"to\": 4956}, {\"ngram\": \"the light\", \"from\": 4968, \"to\": 4977}, {\"ngram\": \"the darkness\", \"from\": 4981, \"to\": 4993}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5031}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 5033, \"to\": 5037}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 5042, \"to\": 5049}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5074}, {\"ngram\": \"the dark\", \"from\": 5078, \"to\": 5086}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADAthen fired backby stating it was \\\"astonished by the outrageous, completely false and defamatory remarks\\\" from Tygart while reiterating its view that it acted appropriately in deciding not to appeal the case.\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5205, \"end\": 5211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADAthen\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5099}, {\"ngram\": \"the outrageous, completely false and defamatory remarks\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5198}, {\"ngram\": \"its view\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5238}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the blowback, WADA on April 25 announced a new review of its process via an independent prosecutor, Eric Cottier.\", \"from\": 5304, \"to\": 5432, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 5307, \"to\": 5315}, {\"ngram\": \"the blowback\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5331}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 5333, \"to\": 5337}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 5341, \"to\": 5346}, {\"ngram\": \"a new review\", \"from\": 5360, \"to\": 5372}, {\"ngram\": \"its process\", \"from\": 5376, \"to\": 5387}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent prosecutor\", \"from\": 5392, \"to\": 5417}, {\"ngram\": \"Eric Cottier\", \"from\": 5419, \"to\": 5431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That also drew criticism from USADA, as WADA hand-picked the Swiss attorney to conduct the review.\", \"from\": 5433, \"to\": 5531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5463, \"end\": 5468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 5494, \"end\": 5499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9920557477863601, \"rank\": 0.008007868267885285, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"criticism\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5457}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 5473, \"to\": 5477}, {\"ngram\": \"the review\", \"from\": 5520, \"to\": 5530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, WADAdefended Cottier's reputationand said he was \\\"entirely independent.\\\"\", \"from\": 5532, \"to\": 5615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADAdefended Cottier's reputationand\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also last week, WADApublished a six-page fact sheetto defend its actions (and inaction) further.\", \"from\": 5617, \"to\": 5713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a six-page fact sheetto\", \"from\": 5647, \"to\": 5670}, {\"ngram\": \